rch 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Ruben Santiago-Hudson]]''', playwright and actor<br> Santiago-Hudson has won national awards for his work in both areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buffalostate.edu/insider/index.asp?article=2760 |title=Insider - Buffalo State College - College Confers Honors on Four Alumni |publisher=Buffalostate.edu |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120517164328/http://www.buffalostate.edu/insider/index.asp?article=2760 |archivedate=17 May 2012 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Mayra Santos-Febres]]''', poet, novelist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gf.org/fellows/16676-mayra-santos-febres |title=Mayra Santos-Febres - John Simon Guggenheim Memorial Foundation |publisher=Gf.org |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103234451/http://www.gf.org/fellows/16676-mayra-santos-febres |archivedate=3 January 2014 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Iv\u00e1n Segarra B\u00e1ez]]''', novelist, poet, author of ''Ante la luz de un amor prohibido'' and director of ''Revista Literaria de Puerto Rico''.\n* '''[[Pedro Juan Soto]]''', writer/novelist<br />'' Soto is the father of slain independence activist [[Carlos Soto Arriv\u00ed]].''<ref name=\"TIME\">{{cite magazine|author=iPad iPhone Android TIME TV Populist The Page |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,916768,00.html |title=Nation: Death at Cerro Maravilla |magazine=TIME |date=14 May 1979 |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Clemente Soto V\u00e9lez]]''', poet and activist<ref name=\"CSV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.centropr.org/faids/velezb.html |title=Guide to the Clemente Soto V\u00e9lez and Amanda V\u00e9lez Papers 1924-1996 (Bulk 1960s-1994) |accessdate=17 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120227101005/http://www.centropr.org/faids/velezb.html |archivedate=27 February 2012 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Clementina Souchet]]''', novelist, author of ''Clementina: Historia sin fin'' (1986)<ref name=Zimmerman/>