a.\" ''El Pa\u00eds'' 9 June 2013.</ref>\n* '''Elidio La Torre-Lagares''' (born 1965), poet, novelist, essayist, author of ''Vicios de construcci\u00f3n'' (2008)<ref name=Torres/>\n* '''[[Tato Laviera]]''', poet<br />''Author of \"AmeR\u00edcan\".''<ref>{{Harvnb|Luis|1992|p=1022}}</ref>\n* '''[[Georgina L\u00e1zaro]]''', children's poet<ref name=\"Leon\">[http://www.hitn.tv/noticia_es.php?id=605 ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080307030023/http://www.hitn.tv/noticia_es.php?id=605 |date=7 March 2008 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Muna Lee (writer)|Muna Lee]]''', writer<br /> ''Born in [[Mississippi]], was the first wife of [[Luis Mu\u00f1oz Mar\u00edn]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uhmc.sunysb.edu/surgery/muna.html |title=Muna Lee: A Pan-American Life |publisher=Uhmc.sunysb.edu |date= |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Aurora Levins Morales]]''' (born 1954), writer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.cla.umn.edu/artistpages/morales_aurora_levins.php |title=Aurora Levins Morales : Voices From the Gaps : University of Minnesota |publisher=Voices.cla.umn.edu |date= |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Jos\u00e9 Liboy Erba (Pepe Liboy)]]''' (born 1964)<ref name=Torres/>\n* '''[[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Lima]]''' (1934\u20132009), poet, philosopher, mathematician, author of ''La s\u00edlaba en la piel'' (1982)<ref name=Torres/><ref>[[:es:Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Lima]]</ref>\n* '''[[Dahlma Llanos Figueroa]]''' (born 1949), writer, author of ''Daughters of the Stone'', nominated and finalist for the 2010 PEN/America Bingham Award<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dahlmallanosfigueroa.com/ |title=Dahlma Llanos Figueroa Official Website |accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref>\n* '''[[Luis Llor\u00e9ns Torres]]''', poet<ref name=\"ND\"/>\n* '''[[Washington Llorens]]''', journalist, writer, [[linguistics|linguist]], and scholar<ref name=\"visitponce\"/><ref>[http://www.enciclopediapr1.org/ing/article.cfm?ref=10011901 ]{{dead link|date=March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Luis L\u00f3pez Nieves]]''', writer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ciudadseva.com/libros/ponce.htm |title=La verdadera muerte de Juan Ponce de Le\u00f3n - Luis L\u00f3pez Nieves |publisher=Ciudadseva.com |date=7 May 2011 |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[\u00c1ngel Lozada]]''', novelist<ref>{{cite journal|last=Villanueva Collado |first=Alfredo |url=http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/pdf/377/37719110.pdf |title=Ren\u00e9 Marqu\u00e9s, Angel Lozada, and the Constitution of the (Queer) Puerto Rican National Subject |publisher=CENTRO Journal 19:1 (Spring 2007), 179&ndash;191 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923055717/http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/pdf/377/37719110.pdf |archivedate=23 September 2012 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Carmen Lugo Filippi]]''' (born 1940), short-story writer<ref name=Torres/>\n{{div col end}}\n\n==M-N==\n{{div col}}\n* '''[[Manuel Manrique]]''', novelist, author of ''Island in Harlem'' (1966)<ref name=Zimmerman/>\n* '''[[Hugo Margenat]]''', poet<br />Margenat was also the founder of the political youth pro-independence organizations \"Acci\u00f3n Juventud Independentista\" and \"Federaci\u00f3n de Universitarios Pro Independencia\".<ref name=\"EPR\">{{cite web |url=http://www.enciclopediapr.org/ing/article.cfm?ref=06100601&page=5 |title=Language and Literature: Brief History of Puerto Rican Literature |publisher=Enciclopediapr.org |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113133453/http://www.enciclopediapr.org/ing/article.cfm?ref=06100601&page=5 |archivedate=13 January 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* '''[[Ren\u00e9 Marqu\u00e9s]]''', playwright<br />''Marqu\u00e9s wrote \"La Carreta\" (The Oxcart) which helped secure his reputation as a leading literary figure in Puerto Rico.''<ref name=\"A\">https://journals.ku.edu/index.php/latr/article/viewFile/63/38</ref> \n* '''[[Manuel Mart\u00ednez Maldonado]]''' (born 1937), physician, poet, novelist, author of poetry books ''La voz sostenida'' and ''