oncemetery.net |date= |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>\n* '''[[Edward Rivera]]''', novelist, author of ''Family Installments: Memories of Growing Up Hispanic'' (1983)<ref name=Zimmerman/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C03E5DE1130F932A3575AC0A9679C8B63 |title=Edward Rivera, 62, Writer and Teacher - NYTimes.com |work=New York Times |date=1 September 2001 |accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref> \n* '''[[Jos\u00e9 Rivera (playwright)|Jos\u00e9 Rivera]]''', playwright<br /> ''Rivera is the first [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]] screenwriter to be nominated for an [[Academy Awards|Oscar]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1433580/awards|title=Jose Rivera}}</ref>\n* '''[[Oswaldo Rivera]]''', novelist, author of ''Fire and Rain'' (1990)<ref name=Zimmerman/>\n* '''[[Abraham Rodriguez|Abraham Rodr\u00edguez, Jr.]]''', short story author; works include ''Ashes to Ashes'' (1989),<ref name=Zimmerman/> ''Boy Without a Flag'', ''Spidertown'', ''The Buddha Book'', ''South by South Bronx''\n* '''[[Leonardo Rodr\u00edguez (author)|Leonardo Rodr\u00edguez]]''', short story author; works include ''They Have to Be Puerto Ricans'' (1988)<ref name=Zimmerman/>\n* '''[[Lola Rodr\u00edguez de Ti\u00f3]]''', poet<br />''Rodr\u00edguez de Ti\u00f3 wrote lyrics to the revolutionary \"[[La Borinque\u00f1a]]\"''.\n* '''[[Edgardo Rodr\u00edguez Juli\u00e1]]''', novelist, author of ''The Renuciation'' and ''Cortijo's Wake''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bibliotecavirtualut.suagm.edu/erj/inicio_erj.html |title=Edgardo Rodr\u00edguez Juli\u00e1 - \u00a1Bienvenidos! |publisher=Bibliotecavirtualut.suagm.edu |accessdate=12 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222170821/http://bibliotecavirtualut.suagm.edu/erj/inicio_erj.html |archivedate=22 February 2014 }}</ref>\n* '''[[Bonafide Rojas]]''', poet, musician, author of ''When the City Sleeps'' (2012)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/blogs/pageviews/2012/04/a-poet-l